      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(ui): show actionable error feedback when config.openFile fails",
        "body": "Fixes #87020\n\n## Problem\nControl UI shows no actionable feedback when `config.openFile` fails in a headless VPS environment:\n- xdg-open fails with \"no method available\" error\n- UI shows no error message to user\n- Users may think the Control UI is broken\n\n## Solution\n\n### 1. Server Side Improvement\nEnhanced error handling in `config.openFile` handler:\n- Detect headless environment errors (`xdg-open` + `no method available`)\n- Provide detailed, actionable error message:\n  - \"Cannot open file in headless environment\"\n  - File path included\n  - Explanation of missing browser handler\n\n### 2. Client Side Improvement\nEnhanced `openConfigFile` in Control UI:\n- Check response `{ ok: false }` properly\n- Display error message via `state.lastError`\n- Copy file path to clipboard as fallback\n- Show actionable feedback to users\n\n### 3. Test Coverage\n- Updated existing gateway test to expect detailed error format\n- Added test for headless environment error detection\n\n## Changes\n- `src/gateway/server-methods/config.ts`: Improved error message formatting with headless detection\n- `ui/src/ui/controllers/config.ts`: Handle ok=false response properly, clear lastError with null\n- `src/gateway/server-methods/config.test.ts`: Updated and added tests for error handling\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior or issue addressed:** `config.openFile` gateway handler now detects headless environment failures (`xdg-open` + `no method available`) and returns actionable error messages. Control UI `openConfigFile` now properly handles `{ ok: false }` responses, displays error to user, and copies config path to clipboard.\n\n- **Real environment tested:** Gateway unit tests verify server-side error detection and message formatting. UI controller code review confirms proper `{ ok: false }` handling with clipboard fallback.\n\n- **Evidence after fix:**\n\n```text\nGateway test: returns actionable headless environment error when xdg-open reports no method available\n\nTest assertion: error === \"Cannot open file in headless environment. File path: /tmp/config.json. This environment appears to lack a graphical or terminal browser handler.\"\n\nTest assertion: respond payload === { ok: false, path: \"/tmp/config.json\", error: \"...actionable message...\" }\n\nGateway test: returns a detailed error and logs details when the opener fails\n\nTest assertion: error === \"Failed to open config file: spawn xdg-open ENOENT\"\n```\n\nUI controller behavior (code path verified):\n- `state.lastError = null` clears previous error (matching `string | null` type contract)\n- `if (!res.ok)` checks failure response\n- `state.lastError = errorMessage` displays error\n- `navigator.clipboard.writeText(path)` copies path as fallback\n- Error message includes clipboard status\n\n- **Observed result after fix:** Gateway returns `{ ok: false, path, error }` with actionable message for both generic opener failures and detected headless environment errors. UI displays error and provides clipboard fallback for config path.\n\n- **What was not tested:** Live headless VPS environment screenshot (tested via gateway unit tests and code review of UI error handling).\n\n## Verification\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/gateway/server-methods/config.test.ts` - 16 tests pass\n- `pnpm build` - successful\n- `pnpm check:changed -- --base upstream/main` - passes",
